# Cursor/Codex AI Rules for BIMIndex

## Guidelines
- Tri-Modal routing is the core priority. Optimize for Rust (Tantivy/LanceDB) and Python integrations.
- Always use Antigravity subagents for running parallel queries.
- Incorporate RRF (Reciprocal Rank Fusion) with k=60 natively in the final step.

## Task List
- Read `TASKS.md` for 10 detailed tasks with specs and implementation steps.

## Model Routing
- Read `ROUTING.md` before any task.
- Live DB integrations (Tantivy/LanceDB/KuzuDB) → Qwen3 Coder Plus write + Pro verify. Run in parallel.
- Standard DB SDK wiring (Neo4j, PaddleOCR) → DeepSeek V4 Flash.
- Novel retrieval algorithms (SPLADE, cross-encoder, PageIndex) → DeepSeek V4 Pro.
- CI/CD, docs → DeepSeek V4 Flash.
- Run `PYTHONPATH=. pytest tests/ -v` after any change — 79 tests must pass.
